When does Orson Welles make _Batman_?

He dies October 10, 1985, so he is not around for the latest string of
Batman movies. If he had the financing for the set design, music, and
costuming of  the Tim Burton et al flicks, I would think that Welles
would accept the challenge. I think _Orson Welles' Batman_ would not
surpass Burton's film in quality.

In the 1960s, Welles is deep into his "I am an unappreciated genius and
I will nver make a picture than ordinary American may like" phase. He
impoverished himself and wasted a decade on _Chimes at Midnight_ a
composite script by Shakespeare starring Welles as Falstaff.

He was offered villain roles in the Adam West _Batman_ but never
returned the calls. Orson Welles was the first choice for King Tut
(replaced by Victor Bruno) and  Mr. Freeze (replaced by George Sanders
and later Otto Preminger).

Or are we talking about the Young Welles. Forget Citizen Caine --- we
have _BatMan_. This is an impossibility given the Hollywood  milieu of
the time. No studio is going to finance a kid's   serial if it costs
more than $20,000 a reel (eight, ten minutes screentime).You could not
convince a mogul to make an honest to God feature from anything as "pop"
as BatMan.
